      ],
      "task_description": {
        "problem": "Assess safety risks for planetary gearbox component-specific faults and generate component-targeted zsafety policies.",
        "steps": "1) Load PlanetaryPdM test data. 2) Classify faults and localize components (sun gear, planet gear, ring gear). 3) Assess gearbox safety by component using assess_gearbox_safety(components=['sun_gear', 'planet_gear', 'ring_gear'], safety_factors=['load_capacity', 'failure_cascade', 'operational_safety']). 4) Check mechanical standards compliance using check_mechanical_standards(components=components, standards=['AGMA_2001', 'ISO_6336']). 5) Generate component-specific safety policies using generate_component_specific_policies(component_faults=localizations, safety_assessment=assessment, standards=standards). 6) Rank components by safety criticality. 7) Output JSON report with fault classifications, component localizations, per-component safety assessment, compliance status, component-specific policies, and criticality rankings."
      },
      "fuzzy_description": "Planetary gearboxes have complex structures, and faults in different components have different safety implications. Can you classify the faults and identify which component (sun gear, planet, ring gear) is affected, assess safety risks for each component type, check compliance with AGMA and ISO gear standards, and generate component-specific safety policies? I need to know which components are most critical for safety.",
      "dependency_analysis": "Load data -> classify and localize faults -> assess safety per component -> check standards -> generate component policies -> rank by criticality.",
